  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPa26">
<l>mālē. maṇivaṇṇā. mārkaḻi nīrāṭuvāṉ</l>
<l>mēlaiyār ceyvaṉakaḷ vēṇṭuvaṉa kēṭṭiyēl</l>
<l>ñālattai ellām naṭuṅka muralvaṉa</l>
<l>pāl aṉṉa vaṇṇattuṉ pāñca caṉṉiyamē</l>
<l>pōlvaṉa caṅkaṅkaḷ pōyp pāṭuṭaiyaṉavē</l>
<l>cālap perum paṟaiyē pallāṇṭicaippārē</l>
<l>kōla viḷakkē koṭiyē vitāṉamē</l>
<l>āliṉ ilaiyāy aruḷēlōr empāvāy</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O Māl! O sapphire-coloured One!</l>
<l>If You ask [us] what is required for</l>
<l>the rites of the superior people for the Mārkaḻi bathing:</l>
<l>Grant [us]</l>
<l rend="indent">Conches like Your Pāṅcajanya of a milk-like hue</l>
<l rend="indent">that sound in such a way that the whole world shakes,</l>
<l rend="indent">Very big, spacious drums,</l>
<l rend="indent">Those who sing ‘pallāṇtu’,</l>
<l rend="indent">Beautiful lamps, flags, canopies,</l>
<l>O [You] of the banyan-tree leaf!</l>
<l>O our maidens, accept [and] consider [this] attentively!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
